Description: Egypt, avenue of sphinx sculptures leading towards entrance of temple at Karnak. Desert setting. Adult and child walking between sphinxes. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: These sphinxes appear to be part ram, part lion. J M Hudson, 27/01/1998. Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
